Package au.edu.anu.twcore.ecosystem.runtime.containers

Interface ResettableContainer<T>

All Superinterfaces:
Container, fr.cnrs.iees.identity.Identity, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Resettable
All Known Implementing Classes:
CategorizedContainer, ComponentContainer, DescribedContainer
public interface ResettableContainer<T> extends Container
An interface for containers that can be reset to an initial state. Such containers maintain an initial content that can replace their current content when a reset method is called.
Author:
Jacques Gignoux - 16 janv. 2020

    • initialForItem

      T initialForItem​(String id)
      Initial items are used by ResettableContainer to construct their runtime list of items This usually implies a cloning of the initial items to runtime items. This method finds the initial item of which its argument is the clone (if still present - at runtime, items may come and go).
      Parameters:
      id - the unique id of the runtime item
      Returns:
      the initial item of which the previous is the clone, null if nothing found
